{
  "texts": [
    "While manual digitization is subjective and time-consuming, automatic landmarking may not locate the landmarks precisely and may introduce further errors during asymmetry evaluation.",
    "When employing a morphometric approach, the cost of the software and hardware and the need for additional training should not be overlooked [4, 15, 58].",
    "Although the morphometric approach may be quicker to implement, it may not be cost-effective.",
    "On the other hand, as the technique is less landmark-dependent and more reliable, it may improve diagnosis and reduce treatment planning time.",
    "In this regard, voxel-based morphometric MSP [25] could be a viable option for asymmetry assessment."
  ]
}